Description: Some of the most obscure Soviet models were made in Erevan, Armenia. It took some serious research to identify these beasts, because the Erevan factory models almost never have any logos on them. Some originally had small pickguard stencils, but most of these rubbed off and became invisible long ago. Here's a rare example of an Armenian guitar that still retains its logo. The model is called "Krunk", which is Armenian for "Crane" (a large bird). Guitar, produced the Yerevan factory of musical instruments since 1972. the last century.A small deck, the shape vaguely reminiscent FENDER Jazzmaster Working condition. Output - 1/4 jack MADE IN USSR The guitar has signs of wear. Guitar in good working order, but the instruments of the USSR, more than the exhibits and collections, so sold as is, no return or refund.
